        <h3>How to Perform Breast Self-Examination (BSE)</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Stand in front of a mirror with arms at your sides.</li>
          <li>Look for changes in size, shape, or skin texture.</li>
          <li>Use your fingers to gently feel the breast in circular motions.</li>
          <li>Check both breasts and the underarm area.</li>
          <li>Perform once every month.</li>
        </ol>
      </article>

      <article class="article-section">
        <h3>Screening & Early Detection</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Monthly Breast Self-Examination (BSE)</li>
          <li>Clinical breast exams by healthcare professionals</li>
          <li>Mammograms for women aged 40+ or earlier if high risk</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

